# The image build COPYs nothing into the image — the repo is bind-mounted at
# build/run time (see Makefile / Dockerfile). So send an essentially empty build
# context: `docker build` stays fast and never ships the ~19 MB of canonical
# PostScript, the figures, or the git history to the daemon.
#
# If a future Dockerfile adds a COPY, un-ignore that path with a `!` rule below.
*
!Dockerfile
